commit.message: hi hello apparently new file needed to be added idk just wanted to be labeled as contributor lol

Fix highlight Marker not showing

Previous change of using marker visibility didn't work; tempMarker must
be attached and removed everytime.

Schedule initialization initializes in order

Schedule will be sorted on initial getEvents as well as just in adding
events.

Set default no-event location and zoom

With no events, the default is now at UMD at a zoom level of 0.

Fix deletion of events and labels

Deleting an event will delete that specific event. Used to be that the
first EventSlot would be deleted, while the actual event is still
deleted from the database. Then, the label would still linger. Now,
labels are deleted with the marker, and the correct EventSlot is now
deleted.

Stop insertion of existing events on startup

When Schedule is initialized it makes a bunch of new Events, which are
attempted to be registered into the database. By forcing them to use the
empty Event() constructor, and modifiying the fields by access, they are
not placed in the database.

Fix adding events not saving to database

Added committing instead of auto-commit to fix a bunch of 'database
locked' or other weird insertion errors.

Move update/delete functionality to EventDetail

CalendarStreetGUI used to pass EventDetail the methods it would need to
edit the schedule. This got ridiculous; now, the functionality for
updating, cancelling, adding, and deleting are contained in
EventDetail.java

Clean up deletion of markers and labels

Move the resizing of maps out of deletion or addition of markers. Use an
iterators to remove markers as you iterate, and detach them from the
map.
Set lower limit to zoom
Add db log messages, and closed proper connections
